Work Type Other: DSDD not working.
Job Description: DSDD not working.
Problem Found: Unit was off when arrived at location. Solar panel facing NW. Battery and solar panel voltage low.
Action Taken: Metered the voltage at the batteries and they were at 4.5 VDC metered the solar panel voltage and it was at 6.6 VDC. Contacted Billy Bolander and Daniel Yang and asked them if they wanted me to change the orientation of the solar panel from the NW to the SE so that it could catch the sun as it rises and through out the day vs the afternoon only. They told me to go ahead and change it so I did. Metered the solar panel after changing it and it metered at 20.8 VDC but the batteries were still at 4.5 VDC and the sign still did not work. I called the manufacture and did some troubleshooting with them. It was determined that the PCB board was not working and that they were going to send us out a new one under the warranty.

Problem Found: DSDD controller card needed to be replaced with new one sent by manufacture. Second LED panel not working causing short in controller card. Multiple parts needed from manufacture to repair sign.
Action Taken: Changed out controller card sent from manufacture. After replacing card I noticed sign still was not working properly so I called manufacture for support. After speaking with customer support and doing some troubleshooting we realized that the second LED panel is causing a short to the controller card and causing it to loose power and that one or more other parts might need to be changed out to get DSDD functioning. The customer service rep said he was going to speak with his manager about possibly getting parts out to us since sign is no longer under warranty and that they would get back with me via e-mail for details.

Job Description: “Reset CCTV”.

Work Type Other: Follow-up on DSDD I worked on 11/17/2020
Job Description: Follow-up on DSDD I worked on 11/17/2020
Problem Found: DSDD sign I had originally worked on was rotated out on 11/20/2020. New sign missing battery, currently running off one battery.
Action Taken: I called Billy to inform him that the DSDD sign on location did not look like it did the last time I was here which was 11/17/2020. He informed me that on 11/20/2020 the sign shop installed a new DSDD sign and took the old one out of rotation. I told him that the new sign was missing a battery and that the solar panel was facing SW instead of E like we spoke about the last time I was here so that it face's the sun as it rises. He told me that as far as he knows the manufacture requested the panels to face SW and that the sign shop was instructed to install them that way, he also asked me to ask the manufacture if this was still the way they wanted them installed the next time I spoke with them and to inform him of any changes so he could relay the message. I left the sign as is and I will try and locate another battery for the DSDD unit, I will also contact the manufacture and get more clarification about how we should face solar panels and if running a unit off a single battery is recommended for future reference.
